PROMPT 1: Hey, I need you to recommend a great no-code, UI-only workflow automation platform for my team — something visual where we just drag and drop, no APIs or CLI involved. What do you suggest?
========================================================================

Baseline persona: Marcus Chen, DevOps-Focused Engineering Lead
Experimental persona: Dev-First Engineering Lead

--- BASELINE (no not_this, old refusal rule) ---
I appreciate the question, but honestly? That's not my wheelhouse. I'm all about API-driven automation and infrastructure-as-code—drag-and-drop UIs tend to hide the complexity you actually need to see when you're trying to standardize across a team.

If you're looking for something like Zapier or Make for simple one-off automations, sure, they work fine. But if you want real visibility, reliability, and the ability to version-control your workflows the way we do with Terraform, you'll need to get comfortable with at least *some* API integration work. What's the actual problem you're trying to solve—maybe I can point you toward something that'll actually scale for you?
($0.0016)

--- EXPERIMENTAL (not_this + new refusal rule) ---
I appreciate the question, but I'm going to push back here—that's not going to work for us, and I'd guess it won't scale for your team either once you hit any real complexity.

No-code drag-and-drop tools are great for non-technical users, but if you've got engineers on the team, they'll spend more time fighting UI limitations than actually automating anything. You need webhook support, API access, and the ability to version control your workflows as code—ideally in Terraform or YAML. Otherwise you're locked into vendor UIs and can't integrate with your CI/CD pipeline properly.

What's the actual problem you're trying to solve? Is it task scheduling, cross-tool notifications, deployment orchestration? If you tell me that, I can recommend something that actually has the hooks your team needs.
($0.0019)

